  <testcase name="lazy_annotation_rules_documented" classname="com.techleadguru.phase1.day11.Day11LazyAndObjectProviderTest" time="0.001">
    <system-out><![CDATA[[DAY 11] @Lazy RULES:
  1. On @Component/@Bean: bean created on first getBean() call.
  2. On @Autowired injection point: a CGLIB proxy is injected at startup,
     real bean created on first method call.
  3. Use @Lazy on one leg of circular dep to break the cycle.
  ObjectProvider<T> RULES:
  1. getObject()       — required, throws if missing
  2. getIfAvailable()  — optional, returns null if missing
  3. getIfUnique()     — returns null if 0 or 2+ beans exist
  4. stream()          — iterate all beans of the type
]]></system-out>
  </testcase>
